            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30289",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Not reproducable...\n\n1.7.8 has no logging at all\nThe next mini release will also not have translation as new features are only allowed with Minor releases.\n\nThe next minor release does logging on untranslated messages when you set the proper options (log and logUntranslated)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-21T02:42:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-21T02:42:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/30290",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Just to note:\nTo call \"isTranslated()\" which behaves exactly the same (and has internally almost the same code) instead of calling translate() when there is no translatable message is a performance neg...\n\nIn such cases, the translation should be done anyway, as long as both methods are working the same way (strict or loose).\n\nExample:\n{code}\n$var = 'String';\nif ($translate->isTranslated($var)) {\n    $var = $translate->translate($var);\n}\n\/\/ looks two times for the translation array... useless\n\n$var = $translate->($var);\n\/\/ looks only ONCE AND RETURNS 'String' (the Original) when the message can not be translated\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-04-21T02:48:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-04-21T02:48:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
